---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Carcin.ai — Lucas Sommer" description="AI-powered marketing platform that handles strategy, execution, and reporting. Built by Lucas Sommer, productizing 15 years of agency experience.">

  <article class="project-detail container">

    <a href="/projects" class="back-link">&larr; All Projects</a>

    <div class="project-hero">
      <div class="project-icon-lg" style="background:var(--status-building-bg); color:var(--status-building-text);">Ca</div>
      <div>
        <h1>Carcin.ai</h1>
        <span class="project-status status-building">Building</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="project-lede">
      AI-powered marketing platform that handles strategy, execution, and reporting for businesses. The next evolution of the digital agency — productized, automated, and built to scale.
    </p>

    <div class="project-tags-lg">
      <span class="tag">AI</span>
      <span class="tag">Marketing</span>
      <span class="tag">SaaS</span>
      <span class="tag">carcin.ai</span>
    </div>

    <div class="detail-grid">
      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>What is Carcin.ai?</h2>
        <p>Carcin.ai is what happens when 15 years of running a marketing agency meets modern AI. Instead of hiring an agency and waiting weeks for a strategy deck, businesses onboard through a conversational chat experience that captures their brand, audience, and goals — then Carcin.ai builds and executes the marketing plan across 103 channels.</p>
        <p>It's the agency model, productized. Strategy, content, SEO, paid media, email, social — all orchestrated by AI with human oversight where it matters.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Origin Story</h2>
        <p>I've been in marketing since 2011 — starting Socialated (acquired by Virsocom), running attribution at LeadsRx, guest lecturing at Georgetown, writing for MarketingProfs and Forbes, and building <a href="/projects/ad-apt">Ad-Apt</a> into a 15-year agency serving brands like Netflix, Benchmade, Circle K, and Payless.</p>
        <p>The pattern I kept seeing: businesses need sophisticated marketing but can't afford agency retainers, and DIY tools require expertise to use well. The gap between "hire an agency" and "figure it out yourself" is massive. After working with hundreds of companies across every channel, I realized the playbook could be encoded into AI — not to replace strategists, but to make their output accessible to everyone.</p>
        <p>Carcin.ai is the distillation of everything I've learned about what actually works in marketing, delivered through technology instead of headcount.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <p>Small and mid-size businesses need sophisticated marketing but can't afford a $10K/month agency retainer. DIY tools exist but require expertise to use well. The gap between "hire an agency" and "figure it out yourself" is enormous — and that's where Carcin.ai sits.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Chat-based onboarding</strong> — Captures business type, brand tone, audience, competitors, and priorities through conversation</li>
          <li><strong>103-channel framework</strong> — Hub & Spoke marketing strategy covering every acquisition channel</li>
          <li><strong>AI execution</strong> — Content generation, campaign management, and reporting automated via Anthropic API and custom pipelines</li>
          <li><strong>Human in the loop</strong> — Team oversight on strategy, client relationships, and quality</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Proven Results (via Ad-Apt)</h2>
        <p>Carcin.ai productizes the same methodology that produced real results for real brands at <a href="/projects/ad-apt">Ad-Apt</a>:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Payless ShoeSource</strong> — 400% ROAS, 1,200% e-commerce growth</li>
          <li><strong>Teton Gravity Research</strong> — 7.2x ROAS on paid campaigns</li>
          <li><strong>True Blue Car Wash</strong> — $1M+ new sales, 500% subscription growth</li>
          <li><strong>16 law firms</strong> — phones ringing daily with inquiries for over a decade</li>
          <li><strong>Netflix, Circle K, Benchmade, Timberline Lodge</strong> — national brand campaigns</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The playbook works. Carcin.ai encodes it into software so every business can access it — not just the ones that can afford $10K/month retainers.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Team</h2>
        <div class="team-grid">
          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-name">Lucas Sommer</div>
            <div class="team-role">Founder</div>
            <p>15 years in marketing. Built Socialated (acquired), Ad-Apt, ran marketing at LeadsRx (acquired by Unbounce). Forbes, NBC News, Georgetown lecturer.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-name">Bryan Lozano</div>
            <div class="team-role">Co-Founder</div>
            <p>Co-founder of Ad-Apt. Partner in Lucas Sommer Inc. Deep expertise in paid media, client strategy, and campaign execution.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-name">Kody</div>
            <div class="team-role">Development</div>
            <p>Platform development, Zoho integrations, and technical infrastructure.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="team-card">
            <div class="team-name">Humberto</div>
            <div class="team-role">Operations</div>
            <p>Campaign operations, client onboarding, and execution workflows.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>Current Status</h2>
        <p>Actively building. Core platform in development. Zoho integrations live. Landing page and sign-up pipeline operational. Working on the master marketing plan and go-to-market execution.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-section">
        <h2>The Vision</h2>
        <p>Make world-class marketing accessible to every business. Not by dumbing it down, but by automating the execution layer so the strategy can be sophisticated without the overhead.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="updates-section">
      <h2>Updates</h2>
      <div class="update-item">
        <div class="update-date">May 2026</div><div class="update-title">Rebranded from Onit to Carcin.ai</div><p class="update-body">The platform now lives at carcin.ai. Same productized-agency thesis — AI that builds and runs a small business&apos;s entire web presence — under a name that doesn&apos;t collide with the orchestrator persona.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="email-capture">
      <h3>Follow Carcin.ai</h3>
      <p class="capture-sub">Get updates as we build the AI marketing platform — product progress, launches, and lessons learned.</p>
      <form class="email-form">
        <input type="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />
        <button type="submit">Get updates</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <!-- Related Projects -->
    <div class="related-projects">
      <h2>Related Projects</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/projects/ad-apt" class="related-card">
          <div class="related-icon" style="background:rgba(124,58,237,0.12); color:#a78bfa;">Aa</div>
          <div><div class="related-name">Ad-Apt</div><div class="related-desc">The agency that inspired Carcin.ai — 15 years of client results</div></div>
        </a>
        <a href="/projects/monkey-business" class="related-card">
          <div class="related-icon" style="background:var(--surface-2); font-size:1.2rem;">&#x1F412;</div>
          <div><div class="related-name">Monkey Business</div><div class="related-desc">The entrepreneurial mindset behind building Carcin.ai</div></div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @import '../../styles/project-detail.css';

  .team-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .team-card {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .team-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
  }

  .team-name {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .team-role {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .team-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .team-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
